items.headline: Flames at Hurricanes preview
items.subhead: Peters, Lindholm, Hanifin return to Carolina; Calgary seeks ninth win in past 11
items.seoTitle: Calgary Flames Carolina Hurricanes game preview
items.seoDescription: Bill Peters returns to Raleigh to coach against his former team when the Calgary Flames visit the Carolina Hurricanes at PNC Arena on Sunday.Peters had a 137-138-53 record in four seasons with Carolina before resigning and being named coach of the Flames on April 23.Forward Elias Lindholm and defenseman Noah Hanifin also will play at Carolina for the first time since they were traded to Calgary for defenseman Dougie Hamilton, forward Micheal Ferland and defenseman prospect Adam Fox on June 23.
items.seoKeywords: Calgary, Flames, Carolina, Hurricanes, NHL, hockey, game preview, Bill Peters, Elias Lindholm, Noah Hanifin
items.preview:
FLAMES (33-14-5) at HURRICANES (25-20-6) 

2 p.m. ET; SN360, FS-SE, NHL.TV 

 

The Game 

Bill Peters returns to Raleigh to coach against his former team when the Calgary Flames visit the Carolina Hurricanes at PNC Arena on Sunday.

items.headline: Former Hurricanes lift Flames to victory in Carolina
items.subhead: Lindholm, Ryan, Hanifin score to help Calgary to ninth win in 11 games
items.seoTitle: Calgary Flames Carolina Hurricanes game recap
items.seoDescription: Elias Lindholm, Derek Ryan and Noah Hanifin scored against their former team to help the Calgary Flames to a 4-3 win against the Carolina Hurricanes at PNC Arena on Sunday.
items.seoKeywords: Game recap, Calgary Flames, Carolina Hurricanes, February 3, NHL, hockey, Elias Lindholm, Noah Hanifin, Derek Ryan

items.preview: RALEIGH, N.C. -- Elias Lindholm, Derek Ryan and Noah Hanifin scored against their former team to help the Calgary Flames to a 4-3 win against the Carolina Hurricanes at PNC Arena on Sunday.
